As a bit of a jaded and cynical individual, I feel I should begin by suggesting that you not be dissuaded by the campy name.  The manager seems to genuinely care about his establishment, and it shows.  The Slouvaki alone is well worth the trip.  As someone who considers feta cheese his personal kryptonite, I feel I would be remiss to not suggest the feta burger.  The wait staff is VERY attentive and helpful.  Combine all of this with a clean and attractive atmosphere, and you have found a great dining experience.

